    <PrimAttribute name="eDIUnprocDefaultExpiry" id="cc53f63d-ca03-4a63-85db-8d2803227dc6">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>Default number of days unprocessed EDI will be kept.  For the EDI Data types to which it applies this 
setting overrides the default EDI purge period.

Overriden by eDIUnprocBookExpiry, eDIUnprocCusResExpiry, eDIUnprocOperStopExpiry, eDIUnprocReleaseExpiry.

Actual behaviour depends on whether any EDI TIs have processed for the EDI Data.

* If no EDI TIs have been processed then the EDI Data can be deleted.
* If a sub-set of EDI TIs have been processed then the EDI Data is not a candidate for re-processing.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
